# CLAUDE.md Template for Product Marketing Managers

> **What is this?** This is your CLAUDE.md file — the context layer that makes every AI-assisted PMM skill dramatically better. Claude Code reads this file at the start of every session. If this file is weak, every downstream output is weak. If it's dialed in, Claude operates like a PMM who's been at your company for 6 months.
>
> **How to use it:** Copy this file into the root of your project directory as `CLAUDE.md`. Fill in every section. Be specific — vague inputs produce vague outputs. This should take about an hour if you do it properly. That hour pays for itself on every single skill run.
>
> **What to skip:** If a section doesn't apply yet (e.g., you don't have competitive intel), leave the placeholder and come back. An incomplete CLAUDE.md is still 10x better than no CLAUDE.md.

---

## About You

<!-- Who are you and what's your context? This helps Claude calibrate its
     communication style, depth, and assumptions. -->

```
Role:           [Your title — e.g., "Senior PMM at Acme"]
Scope:          [What you own — e.g., "Messaging, positioning, launches for the core product"]
Team size:      [Solo PMM / team of X / embedded in a pod]
Reports to:     [CMO / VP Marketing / Head of Product / etc.]
Experience:     [Years in PMM / marketing — helps calibrate jargon level]
Working style:  [How you prefer to work with AI — fast and messy? Structured? Iterative?]
```

