## Your Voice and Tone

<!-- How your brand sounds. This calibrates Claude's writing style
     for all copy outputs. -->

```
Voice:      [e.g., "Direct, confident, slightly irreverent. We sound like a
             smart colleague, not a corporation."]
Tone:       [e.g., "Warm but no-BS. We don't hedge. We don't use buzzwords.
             We say what we mean."]
Formality:  [Casual / Professional-casual / Professional / Formal]
Jargon:     [e.g., "Use industry terms (ARR, ICP, GTM) freely — our audience
             knows them. Avoid internal jargon (project codenames, internal
             tool names)."]
```

### Words We Use

- [e.g., "simple" not "streamlined"]
- [e.g., "fast" not "accelerated"]
- [e.g., "built for [persona]" not "designed to empower"]

### Words We Never Use

- [e.g., "synergy", "leverage" (as a verb), "disruptive"]
- [e.g., "we're excited to announce" — the reader doesn't care about our emotions]
- [e.g., "best-in-class" — unverifiable]
- [e.g., "solution" without specifying what it solves]

