## Rules for Claude

<!-- Specific instructions for how Claude should behave when working
     with your content. Add rules as you learn what works. -->

1. **Always use [Company Name] exactly as written** — not lowercase, not abbreviated, not paraphrased.
2. **Never fabricate customer quotes or metrics.** If you don't have proof, say so — don't invent it.
3. **Never claim capabilities we don't have.** Check the "What You Don't Do" section before making feature claims.
4. **Match the voice guide.** Every piece of copy should sound like it came from the same brand.
5. **Default to specific over generic.** "Saves 5 hours/week" beats "saves time." Always.
6. [Add your own rules as you discover what Claude gets wrong or right]
